{ Butterfly World}opened{Easter 1984. The owners opened Butterfly World because they farm here,in Yockleton and were looking for something extra to do and they liked wildlife.
They have{70 Tropical species}of butterfly and{30 British species}of butterfly.At present they are establishing more British butterfly habitats. At present the biggest butterfly is the{Owl Moth butterfly} with a wing span of 6 inches. The Tropical species of butterfly were initially{imported from farms in {Taiwan and the Phillipines. { The site also has a piece of preserved meadow land.
